commit_message:
[Services] redesign metaclass to support subclasses

Previous implementation restricts to create Mixin classes and it leds to
duplicate a bunch of code.

Restricted code:

   class SomeService(Service):
       def some_func(self):
           self._impl.some_func()

       def another_func(self):
           self._impl.another_func()

   class SomeMixin(object):
       def some_func(self): <- this method is common for several versions
           # do something

   class SomeV1(SomeService, SomeMixin):
       def another_func(self):
           # do something

   class SomeV2(SomeService, SomeMixin):
       def another_func(self):
           # do something

   class SomeV3(SomeService):
       def some_func(self):
           # do something

       def another_func(self):
           # do something

Instead of requiring all methods to be overridden and hardcode several
exceptions, it would be nice to provide more simplier way(similar to abstract
classes) to do it - simple decorator to mark which methods should be
implemented in subclasses

